Designed to facilitate key programming to VAG NEC clocks on the bench in conjunction with Abrites AVDI and similar programming tools.
When all keys are lost on vehicles with this type of cluster, the EEPROM will need to be read and placed in service mode. A rig helps programme keys without the car being present and prevents components on the car corrupting, which can happen when placing the cluster back in to the car half way through the procedure.

NEC clusters are known to be fitted from 2007 and become more common on cars after 2009.

Professionally made, designed and constructed here in the UK.

All components are RoHS compliant and every unit is carefully inspected and tested on 3 seperate sets of clocks before it leaves the workshop.

Full 12 month guarantee

Connection to a 12v battery using the supplied generous lead length of 750mm fitted with 2x 54mm crocodile clips.

Cross Reference:

The Silca FO21BLR10 is a blue 3 button tibbe key remote with a 6F-63 transponder chip to suit Ford Transit Vans. It is a high quality aftermarket product from Silca and has a similar design to the original key. The key features three function buttons (lock, unlock & boot open), has a replaceable battery and can be programmed with Smart Pro. If necessary, the remote can be reset following the instructions found in MYKEYS Pro. Search FO21BLR10 in the section All Keys Catalogue, click on the key photo and select ‘Download PDF’.
